author: John King
title: A Mission Bay pump station delivers chic design
text:
Photo: John King, The Chronicle Mission Bay's Stormwater Pump Station #6 is one of the smallest -- but most distinctive -- structures in the emerging neighborhood near AT&T Park. The architect is the firm Tom Eliot Fisch. Mission Bay's Stormwater Pump Station #6 is one of the smallest --...
Whatever its flaws might be, the lumpy Mission Bay landscape shows the wisdom of putting care into public buildings, no matter their purpose or size.
